-- Hungary Stocks: Est Media, OTP, Magyar Telekom Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-17T15:40:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/hungary-stocks-est-media-magyar-telekom-are-active-in-budapest.html
Hungary’s benchmark  BUX (BUX)  stock index
rose for a second day, up 1.3 percent to 17,594.98 by the close
in Budapest.  The following rose or fell in the Hungarian market today.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Est Media Vagyonkezelo Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian
entertainment company, fell for a second day after the company
said yesterday it will issue bonds to help refinance debt. The
shares dropped 9.2 percent to 99 forint today after a 4.4
percent decline in the previous session.  Magyar Telekom (MTEL HB), Hungary’s former monopoly
controlled by Deutsche Telekom AG, rose as much as 0.9 percent
to 557 forint before paring its earlier gain to close unchanged
at 552 forint.  Magyar Telekom (MTEL)  shareholders yesterday approved a
50 forint per share dividend.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, jumped
2.9 percent to 3,522 forint. The  International Monetary Fund 
raised its global growth forecast and concern Europe’s debt
crisis will worsen eased as Spain’s bonds gained. Hungary will
manage to obtain a bailout from the IMF, Raiffeisen Bank
International AG said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
